        <h1>LeetCode 1578: Minimum Time to Make Rope Colorful (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Alice has n balloons arranged on a rope. You are given a 0-indexed string colors where colors[i] is the
                color of the ith balloon. Alice wants the rope to be colorful, meaning that no two consecutive balloons
                are of the same color. You are given a 0-indexed integer array neededTime where neededTime[i] is the
                time
                (in seconds) that Alice needs to remove the ith balloon from the rope. Return the minimum time Alice
                needs
                to make the rope colorful.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: colors = "abaac", neededTime = [1,2,3,4,5] → Output: 3. Remove the balloon at index 2 (time = 3)
                and the balloon at index 4 (time = 5). After removal, colors = "abac" which is colorful.
                Input: colors = "abc", neededTime = [1,2,3] → Output: 0. The rope is already colorful, no balloons need
                to be removed.
                Input: colors = "aabaa", neededTime = [1,2,3,4,1] → Output: 2. Remove balloons at indices 1 and 3.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int minCost(string s, vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; time) {
        int total = 0;          // Total time to remove balloons
        int maxTime = time[0];  // Max time in the current same-color group
        for (int i = 1; i &lt; s.size(); ++i) {
            if (s[i] == s[i - 1]) {
                // If two adjacent balloons have the same color,
                // remove the one with smaller time (keep the costliest one).
                total += min(maxTime, time[i]);
                // Update the current group's max removal time
                maxTime = max(maxTime, time[i]);
            } else {
                // New color starts → reset maxTime
                maxTime = time[i];
            }
        }
        return total; // Minimum total time to make all colors alternate
    }
};</code></pre>
